SIMPLE: protractor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Protractor
<hw>Pro*tract"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, protracts, or causes protraction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mathematical instrument for laying down and
measuring angles on paper, used in drawing or in plotting. It is of
various forms, semicircular, rectangular, or circular.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>An instrument formerly used in
extracting foreign or offensive matter from a wound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A muscle which extends an organ
or part; -- opposed to <contr>retractor</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>An adjustable pattern used by tailors.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protreptical</ent>⟦br⟧
